  <Summary>The Treasure of Abbot Thomas: Somerton goes searching for the legendary treasure of Abbot Thomas and finds it buried within a well; however, there is something lurking inside the burial site to ward off invaders.

Oh, Whistle, and I'll Come to You, My Lad: Parkins discovers an old whistle and blows upon it; the whistle summons forth a ghostly creature which stealthily invades Parkins' room.

Count Magnus: Investigating the tomb of Count Magnus, Wraxall idly wishes he could meet him; his wish comes true.

Number 13: While researching documents in Viborg, Anderson stays at a hotel in room 12. At night, he sees a room numbered '13' adjacent to his but he can't find it by daylight. Within the room, Anderson keeps hearing weird noises and sees frightening shadows reflected from the windows. When the man in room 14 finally confronts Anderson to complain about the noise they confront room 13 and see a terrifying creature within.

</Summary>
